article.headline: Villanova two shy of league record for 3-pointers
article.linkText: Villanova uses 16 3-pointers to put away Syracuse
article.story:
SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) -- Katie Davis scored 23 points and Kelly
Nash had 17 as No. 22 Villanova beat Syracuse 71-44 Saturday.

	   Villanova (17-4, 7-3 Big East) made 16 3-pointers, two short of
its league record set in 2001. Davis had seven 3-pointers and Nash
added five.

	   Trish Juhlin added 12 points with two 3-pointers for Villanova.

	   Shannon Perry and Julie McBride led Syracuse (8-13, 3-7) with 12
points each. April Jean added 11.

	   The Orangewomen made just one of their first 12 field-goal
attempts against a Villanova defense that ranks sixth nationally in
scoring.

	   Syracuse's first field goal came more than seven minutes into
the game. Villanova led 11-0 at one point, then missed 17 of its
next 18 shots. Syracuse managed to get as close as 14-13 before
Davis and Nash made back-to-back 3-pointers.

	   Leading 23-18 at halftime, the Wildcats blew the game open to
start the second half with seven straight 3-pointers, four of them
by Davis. The Wildcats made nine of 16 3-pointers in the second half
to win their third straight game.
